sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the Russell 3000 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Salesforce.com Inc (Symbol: CRM), where a total volume of 21,434 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 2.1 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 41.8% of CRM's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 5.1 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $160 strike call option expiring February 22, 2019 , with 1,896 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 189,600 underlying shares of CRM.

ION Geophysical Corp (Symbol: IO) saw options trading volume of 653 contracts, representing approximately 65,300 underlying shares or approximately 41.5% of IO's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 157,365 shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $17.50 strike call option expiring August 16, 2019 , with 250 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 25,000 underlying shares of IO.

Below is a chart showing IO's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $17.50 strike highlighted in orange:

And Reata Pharmaceuticals Inc (Symbol: RETA) options are showing a volume of 697 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 69,700 underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 41.4% of RETA's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 168,380 shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $75 strike put option expiring April 18, 2019 , with 300 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 30,000 underlying shares of RETA.
